==Japanese==

{{ja-kanjitab|安|心}}

===Alternative forms===
* [[安神]]
* [[安心する]]
* [[安心な]]

===Etymology===
From {{term|安|lang=ja|sc=Jpan|tr=an||be at ease}} + {{term|心|lang=ja|sc=Jpan|tr=shin||heart}}

===Noun===
{{ja-noun|k|hira=あんしん|rom=anshin|rs=宀03安}}

# [[relief]], not [[worry]], [[peace of mind]]

====Synonyms====
* [[安堵]] (''ando'')

====Derived terms====
* [[安心感]] (''anshinkan''): sense of security
* [[安心立命]] (''anshin ritsumei''): spiritual peace and enlightenment
* [[一安心]] (''hitoanshin''): feeling of relief
* [[不安心]] (''fuanshin''): uneasiness, uncertainty

====Related terms====
* [[安心立命]] (''anjin-ryūmei'', ''anjin-ryūmyō'', ''anjin-ritsumei''): keeping an unperturbed mind through faith

